\begin{abstract}
Two dimensionless fundamental physical constants, the fine structure constant <TEX_MATH_0> and the proton-to-electron mass ratio <TEX_MATH_1> are attributed a particular importance from the point of view of nuclear synthesis, formation of heavy elements, planets, and life-supporting structures.
['\\documentclass', '[', 'aps,prl,groupedaddress,fleqn,twocolumn,10pt', ']', '{', 'revtex4', '}', '\\pdfoutput=1', '<T_USEPACKAGE_0>', '<T_USEPACKAGE_1>', '<T_USEPACKAGE_2>', '<T_USEPACKAGE_3>', '<T_USEPACKAGE_4>', '<T_USEPACKAGE_5>', '%<T_USEPACKAGE_6>', '\\begin', '{', 'document', '}', '\\raggedbottom', '\\title', '{', 'Speed', 'of', 'sound', 'from', 'fundamental', 'physical', 'constants', '}', '<T_AUTHOR_0>', '<T_AFFILIATION_0>', '<T_AUTHOR_1>', '<T_AFFILIATION_1>%', '<T_AFFILIATION_2>', '<T_AUTHOR_2>', '<T_AFFILIATION_1>%', '<T_AFFILIATION_4>', '<T_AUTHOR_3>', '<T_AFFILIATION_5>', '\\begin', '{', 'abstract', '}', 'Two', 'dimensionless', 'fundamental', 'physical', 'constants', ',', 'the', 'fine', 'structure', 'constant', '<TEX_MATH_0>', 'and', 'the', 'proton-to-electron', 'mass', 'ratio', '<TEX_MATH_1>', 'are', 'attributed', 'a', 'particular', 'importance', 'from', 'the', 'point', 'of', 'view', 'of', 'nuclear', 'synthesis', ',', 'formation', 'of', 'heavy', 'elements', ',', 'planets', ',', 'and', 'life-supporting', 'structures.']
************************************************** 

Here, we show that a combination of these two constants results in a new dimensionless constant which provides the upper bound for the speed of sound in condensed phases, <TEX_MATH_2>.
['Here', ',', 'we', 'show', 'that', 'a', 'combination', 'of', 'these', 'two', 'constants', 'results', 'in', 'a', 'new', 'dimensionless', 'constant', 'which', 'provides', 'the', 'upper', 'bound', 'for', 'the', 'speed', 'of', 'sound', 'in', 'condensed', 'phases', ',', '<TEX_MATH_2>.']
************************************************** 

We find that <TEX_MATH_3>, where <TEX_MATH_4> is the speed of light in vacuum.
['We', 'find', 'that', '<TEX_MATH_3>', ',', 'where', '<TEX_MATH_4>', 'is', 'the', 'speed', 'of', 'light', 'in', 'vacuum.']
************************************************** 

The Bohr radius gives a characteristic scale of interatomic distance on the order of the Angstrom, in terms of electron mass <TEX_MATH_5>, charge <TEX_MATH_6>, and Planck constant <TEX_MATH_7>.
['The', 'Bohr', 'radius', 'gives', 'a', 'characteristic', 'scale', 'of', 'interatomic', 'distance', 'on', 'the', 'order', 'of', 'the', 'Angstrom', ',', 'in', 'terms', 'of', 'electron', 'mass', '<TEX_MATH_5>', ',', 'charge', '<TEX_MATH_6>', ',', 'and', 'Planck', 'constant', '<TEX_MATH_7>.']
************************************************** 

Two important dimensionless constants are the fine structure constant <TEX_MATH_0> and the proton-to-electron mass ratio, <TEX_MATH_1>.
['Two', 'important', 'dimensionless', 'constants', 'are', 'the', 'fine', 'structure', 'constant', '<TEX_MATH_0>', 'and', 'the', 'proton-to-electron', 'mass', 'ratio', ',', '<TEX_MATH_1>.']
************************************************** 

The finely-tuned values of <TEX_MATH_0> and <TEX_MATH_1>, and the balance between them, governs nuclear reactions such as proton decay and nuclear synthesis in stars, leading to the creation of the essential biochemical elements, including carbon.
['The', 'finely-tuned', 'values', 'of', '<TEX_MATH_0>', 'and', '<TEX_MATH_1>', ',', 'and', 'the', 'balance', 'between', 'them', ',', 'governs', 'nuclear', 'reactions', 'such', 'as', 'proton', 'decay', 'and', 'nuclear', 'synthesis', 'in', 'stars', ',', 'leading', 'to', 'the', 'creation', 'of', 'the', 'essential', 'biochemical', 'elements', ',', 'including', 'carbon.']
************************************************** 

This balance provides a narrow ``habitable zone'' in the (<TEX_MATH_0>,<TEX_MATH_1>) space where stars and planets can form and life-supporting molecular structures can emerge <T_CITE_1>.
['This', 'balance', 'provides', 'a', 'narrow', '`', '`', 'habitable', 'zone', "'", "'", 'in', 'the', '(', '<TEX_MATH_0>,<TEX_MATH_1>', ')', 'space', 'where', 'stars', 'and', 'planets', 'can', 'form', 'and', 'life-supporting', 'molecular', 'structures', 'can', 'emerge', '<T_CITE_1>.']
************************************************** 



We show that a simple combination of <TEX_MATH_0> and <TEX_MATH_1> results in another dimensionless quantity which has an unexpected and specific implication for a key property of condensed phases, the speed at which waves travel in solids and liquids, or the speed of sound, <TEX_MATH_8>.
['We', 'show', 'that', 'a', 'simple', 'combination', 'of', '<TEX_MATH_0>', 'and', '<TEX_MATH_1>', 'results', 'in', 'another', 'dimensionless', 'quantity', 'which', 'has', 'an', 'unexpected', 'and', 'specific', 'implication', 'for', 'a', 'key', 'property', 'of', 'condensed', 'phases', ',', 'the', 'speed', 'at', 'which', 'waves', 'travel', 'in', 'solids', 'and', 'liquids', ',', 'or', 'the', 'speed', 'of', 'sound', ',', '<TEX_MATH_8>.']
************************************************** 

We find that this combination provides an upper bound for <TEX_MATH_8>, <TEX_MATH_2>, as
<T_EQUATION_0>
\noindent where <TEX_MATH_4> is the speed of light in vacuum.
