Although bonding in weakly-bonded solids such as noble, molecular and hydrogen-bonded solids is also electromagnetic in origin, weak dipole and van der Waals interactions result in smaller <TEX_MATH_14> <T_CITE_34> and smaller <TEX_MATH_8> as a result.
